      "content": "idk, it feels like people on the other side of the debate act like the safety risks aren't even real, or like they're just being stubborn. but then on the flip side, some people talk about nuclear like it's this perfect silver bullet that fixes everything. is there actually a middle ground or are people just picking sides based on whatever they want to believe?",
